00:31:13.780 --> 00:31:17.567
PHILLIP TAN: Back in the '90s
and even the early 2000s,

00:31:17.567 --> 00:31:18.983
user testing and
usability testing

00:31:18.983 --> 00:31:21.415
were basically the
same thing, because we

00:31:21.415 --> 00:31:23.730
were talking about websites
and enterprise software.

00:31:23.730 --> 00:31:25.142
We were not talking about games.

00:31:25.142 --> 00:31:27.350
So the only kind of user
testing that you'd be doing,

00:31:27.350 --> 00:31:29.540
putting a piece of software
in front of someone,

00:31:29.540 --> 00:31:31.350
getting feedback, was
usability testing.

00:31:31.350 --> 00:31:34.315
That's why they had the
same name for so long.

00:31:34.315 --> 00:31:36.970
But now there's focus testing,
which is very, very applicable

00:31:36.970 --> 00:31:40.523
not just for games but also for
things like user experience.

