AUDIENCE: Hi.

01:10:51.097 --> 01:10:52.180
I'm with Lost Underground.

01:10:52.180 --> 01:10:54.385
As a refresher on
our game, the idea

01:10:54.385 --> 01:10:57.472
is that you are lost underground
in the darkness trying

01:10:57.472 --> 01:10:58.602
to find an exit.

01:10:58.602 --> 01:11:02.665
And so as part of our
game, we have this sphere

01:11:02.665 --> 01:11:04.418
of visibility around you.

01:11:04.418 --> 01:11:07.490
And as we play tested, we
got a lot of good feedback

01:11:07.490 --> 01:11:09.935
on what that visibility
means to people

01:11:09.935 --> 01:11:12.883
and how we can
actually use it to make

01:11:12.883 --> 01:11:15.751
our mechanics and our
[INAUDIBLE] design

01:11:15.751 --> 01:11:16.950
more compelling.

01:11:16.950 --> 01:11:19.614
Another big issue we
ran into with people

01:11:19.614 --> 01:11:24.035
play testing was
our collision boxes

01:11:24.035 --> 01:11:25.430
are basically pixel perfect.

01:11:25.430 --> 01:11:27.180
And so people would
get caught trying

01:11:27.180 --> 01:11:32.370
to go through the map, which
was really helpful for us,

01:11:32.370 --> 01:11:35.017
because although we already
knew that this problem existed,

01:11:35.017 --> 01:11:37.350
we actually learned a lot
about how people were actually

01:11:37.350 --> 01:11:38.844
trying to make these decisions.

01:11:38.844 --> 01:11:40.587
And we learned that
instead of using

01:11:40.587 --> 01:11:43.630
the idea of the entire
[INAUDIBLE], a lot of players

01:11:43.630 --> 01:11:46.330
were actually looking at
where the feet were planted

01:11:46.330 --> 01:11:47.776
and trying to move
based on that.

01:11:47.776 --> 01:11:50.186
So when we go and
fix it, we'll make

01:11:50.186 --> 01:11:53.240
sure to put the collision box
around where the feet are.

01:11:53.240 --> 01:11:56.335
We also got a lot of good
feedback on the items

01:11:56.335 --> 01:11:58.584
that we have in our game and
where people are actually

01:11:58.584 --> 01:12:01.310
focusing their attention.

