01:12:08.044 --> 01:12:09.390
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

01:12:09.390 --> 01:12:10.602
PROFESSOR: Oh, Plunder Winds.

01:12:10.602 --> 01:12:11.102
Yeah.

01:12:17.130 --> 01:12:22.322
AUDIENCE: So our game
involves moving around a grid

01:12:22.322 --> 01:12:24.210
and running into
random encounters.

01:12:27.167 --> 01:12:28.875
The favorability of
the random encounters

01:12:28.875 --> 01:12:32.230
are indicated to the player
by numbers and colors

01:12:32.230 --> 01:12:33.770
on the board.

01:12:33.770 --> 01:12:36.675
So one of the biggest things
that we got from testing

01:12:36.675 --> 01:12:38.100
was that people
didn't understand

01:12:38.100 --> 01:12:39.808
the role of the numbers
and colors played

01:12:39.808 --> 01:12:42.486
or how they were related
or if they were related.

01:12:42.486 --> 01:12:49.025
And they began by moving around
randomly and just waiting

01:12:49.025 --> 01:12:51.138
for things to happen to them.

01:12:51.138 --> 01:12:52.596
There's also a
mechanic in our game

01:12:52.596 --> 01:12:57.347
that involves moving with the
wind and against the wind.

01:12:57.347 --> 01:12:59.430
And so moving with the
wind doesn't count stamina,

01:12:59.430 --> 01:13:02.604
but moving against
the wind does.

01:13:02.604 --> 01:13:04.666
Or moving sideways
of the wind does.

01:13:04.666 --> 01:13:06.332
Moving against the
wind is not possible.

01:13:06.332 --> 01:13:09.110
People had trouble
figuring that out as well.

01:13:09.110 --> 01:13:11.735
So one of the biggest things
we're going to try and do

01:13:11.735 --> 01:13:15.550
is more visual
feedback to the player,

01:13:15.550 --> 01:13:18.352
help them figure
things out as it goes.

01:13:18.352 --> 01:13:19.810
Also, people felt
like there should

01:13:19.810 --> 01:13:23.710
be more long-term consequences
instead of just planning

01:13:23.710 --> 01:13:25.323
for the next move or two.

01:13:25.323 --> 01:13:27.788
And so we're going to see
how we can integrate that

01:13:27.788 --> 01:13:30.253
into our game.

01:13:30.253 --> 01:13:33.704
[APPLAUSE]

01:13:39.620 --> 01:13:40.606
AUDIENCE: Hi.

01:13:40.606 --> 01:13:41.592
Blind Aliens.

01:13:41.592 --> 01:13:43.564
So we got a lot
of great feedback

01:13:43.564 --> 01:13:45.740
from the use play testing.

01:13:45.740 --> 01:13:47.440
So one of the main
things we realized

01:13:47.440 --> 01:13:52.148
is we needed more clear goals
and more long-term goals.

01:13:52.148 --> 01:13:54.549
So for example, our gun
automatically reloads,

01:13:54.549 --> 01:13:56.298
and that was a little
confusing for people

01:13:56.298 --> 01:13:58.960
because they didn't really
see that it was reloading.

01:13:58.960 --> 01:14:00.638
But instead of doing
something like that

01:14:00.638 --> 01:14:02.198
where the gun
automatically reloads,

01:14:02.198 --> 01:14:04.772
we're thinking of adding
bullets around that you

01:14:04.772 --> 01:14:08.490
have to go and collect so it's
more short-term goals and also

01:14:08.490 --> 01:14:09.316
long-term strategy.

01:14:09.316 --> 01:14:12.274
How do you save your bullets
up, when do you use them all.

01:14:12.274 --> 01:14:14.037
Another thing we noticed
was that our game

01:14:14.037 --> 01:14:15.620
was way too hard at
first, and way too

01:14:15.620 --> 01:14:17.069
easy after five minutes.

01:14:17.069 --> 01:14:20.450
So we decided we need to focus
on ramping up the difficulty.

01:14:20.450 --> 01:14:22.623
Instead of starting with
three aliens attacking you,

01:14:22.623 --> 01:14:23.706
maybe only one.

01:14:23.706 --> 01:14:26.080
And then maybe after five
minutes, instead of only having

01:14:26.080 --> 01:14:28.590
three aliens, maybe 10.

01:14:28.590 --> 01:14:32.130
[INAUDIBLE] difficult.

01:14:32.130 --> 01:14:37.486
So another thing we
focused on was our AI.

01:14:37.486 --> 01:14:38.325
Not AI.

01:14:38.325 --> 01:14:39.400
User interface.

01:14:39.400 --> 01:14:42.220
So I talked about how there
was a reloading thing,

01:14:42.220 --> 01:14:44.255
it was flashing in the
corner, but no one saw it

01:14:44.255 --> 01:14:46.250
so no one knew that
their gun was reloading.

01:14:46.250 --> 01:14:48.400
They thought it
just wasn't working

01:14:48.400 --> 01:14:50.677
and they were frustrated
that they were clicking

01:14:50.677 --> 01:14:51.760
and nothing was happening.

01:14:51.760 --> 01:14:53.790
So we need to make
that more visual.

01:14:53.790 --> 01:14:56.245
Along with our aliens,
when they're half-dead

01:14:56.245 --> 01:14:57.610
or they're still attacking you.

01:14:57.610 --> 01:14:58.860
People thought they were dead.

01:14:58.860 --> 01:15:01.580
They'd run into them and
they'd die and be frustrated.

01:15:01.580 --> 01:15:04.940
So instead of maybe
turning them darker,

01:15:04.940 --> 01:15:07.830
maybe turn them red or something
like that to make that clearer.

01:15:07.830 --> 01:15:09.889
So thank you guys
for all the feedback.

01:15:09.889 --> 01:15:13.200
[APPLAUSE]

