01:15:26.105 --> 01:15:32.070
And it's because we're modeling
a 3-D die using 2-D graphics.

01:15:32.070 --> 01:15:34.447
So a lot of people
have different opinions

01:15:34.447 --> 01:15:36.030
about how that should
look, and no one

01:15:36.030 --> 01:15:38.477
thought that the way
it does look is OK.

01:15:38.477 --> 01:15:39.760
[INAUDIBLE]

01:15:39.760 --> 01:15:42.913
And so we really got
a lot of opinions.

01:15:42.913 --> 01:15:44.204
Maybe you could do it this way.

01:15:44.204 --> 01:15:45.495
Maybe you could do it this way.

01:15:45.495 --> 01:15:47.876
And that really
helps, because now we

01:15:47.876 --> 01:15:50.230
can really build up a discussion
of how it should look.

01:15:50.230 --> 01:15:52.820
How we can make this mental
model in people's heads

01:15:52.820 --> 01:15:54.750
match what they're seeing
on the screen, which

01:15:54.750 --> 01:15:57.180
is the real hard challenge
that we're facing.

01:15:57.180 --> 01:15:59.610
So thanks for the feedback.

