01:16:29.282 --> 01:16:31.247
but it wasn't
clear to the player

01:16:31.247 --> 01:16:32.955
exactly how many
beavers you can populate

01:16:32.955 --> 01:16:34.730
or how many dams
you could build,

01:16:34.730 --> 01:16:37.720
or what natural
disasters could happen.

01:16:37.720 --> 01:16:41.526
And then between each turn, when
a natural disaster happened,

01:16:41.526 --> 01:16:43.020
there wasn't that
much engagement

01:16:43.020 --> 01:16:45.880
between the player and
the game being like,

01:16:45.880 --> 01:16:48.302
oh, this drought
happened and then

01:16:48.302 --> 01:16:50.470
this is a consequence of that.

01:16:50.470 --> 01:16:53.970
So I think going forward,
we're going to really try

01:16:53.970 --> 01:16:57.399
to make it easier for players
to understand what happened

01:16:57.399 --> 01:16:59.864
during that turn, and then
what their choices are

01:16:59.864 --> 01:17:01.343
in terms of picking it.

01:17:01.343 --> 01:17:04.794
So a lot of it is clarifying
what the instructions are,

01:17:04.794 --> 01:17:07.752
what the game mechanics are.

